Aegisight AI: MVP Master Execution PlanVersion: 1.2 (Dual-Path Strategy)Focus: Predictive Incident Prevention SystemPersona: Sarah, IT Ops DirectorCore Promise: "We predict the incidents your current tools miss."1. Executive Summary: The Dual-Path MVPWe are splitting the MVP into two distinct modes to accelerate trust and adoption.ModeNameGoalUser ActionOption 1The Risk AuditImmediate Proof. Prove the "Brain" works using historical data without requiring IT permissions.User uploads a CSV file of past incidents/logs. System generates a "Retro-Prediction Report."Option 2The MonitorReal-Time Protection. The scalable product that runs 24/7.User connects ServiceNow API. System provides real-time "Risk Alerts."The "Aha!" MomentAudit Mode: "Wow, you found the exact pattern that caused our outage last month."Monitor Mode: "The system just alerted us to a high CPU spike 2 hours before we usually see tickets."2. Strategic AlignmentComponentStrategic Role (Business)Learning Path Role (Technical)The BrainCore Value. Forecasting failures.BigQuery ML: Mastering ARIMA_PLUS.The Ingest (CSV)Low-Friction Sales. "Try before you integrate."File Handling: Parsing uploads & Bulk Inserts to DB.The Ingest (API)Stickiness. "Set it and forget it."ServiceNow Integration: OAuth & REST API.3. Go-To-Market StrategyStep 1: The "Coffee Shop" Pitch (Option 1)The Hook: "You don't need to install anything. Just export your incident log from last month to CSV."The Process: You meet the partner/client, upload their CSV into your local Aegisight instance.The Result: A generated report showing: "Here are 3 times your system failed. Aegisight predicted all 3 of them 4 hours in advance."Step 2: The "Pilot" Upgrade (Option 2)The Upsell: "Now that you trust the brain, let's turn it on live. We'll connect to your ServiceNow Sandbox today."4. Technical Architecture & Data Flowgraph LR
