5. Execution: The Antigravity Agent InstructionsUse these updated prompts to build the CSV Uploader first (easier/faster), then the ServiceNow Connector.Phase 1: The Simulator (Data Generation)Keep this for your own internal testing.Instruction:Create a standalone script scripts/simulate_data.js.Generate cpu_load (0-100) and ticket_velocity (int) data.Failure Pattern: 10% of the time, CPU > 90% AND Tickets > 10.Save this as sample_data.csv (so we can test the CSV uploader immediately) AND insert into DB.Phase 2: The "Risk Audit" (CSV Importer)New Feature: Immediate Proof of ValueInstruction:Create a new API route POST /api/upload-csv and a simple frontend "Upload" button.Frontend: Allow user to select a CSV file.Backend: Use a stream parser (like fast-csv) to read the file.Validation: Ensure columns timestamp, cpu_load, ticket_velocity exist.Action: Bulk insert valid rows into the BigQuery dataset (or TimescaleDB buffer first).Trigger: Automatically run the Training Query (Phase 3) after upload completes.Phase 3: The Brain (BigQuery ML)Instruction:Create src/models/risk_engine.sql.CREATE OR REPLACE MODEL using ARIMA_PLUS.Train on the data currently in the table (whether from CSV or API).Create a query to DETECT_ANOMALIES with anomaly_probability > 0.75.Phase 4: The "Monitor" (ServiceNow Connector)The Scalable FeatureInstruction:Create a service src/services/servicenow.js.Use axios with Basic Auth (credentials in .env).Fetch incidents from /api/now/table/incident (Last 30 days).Normalization: Map ServiceNow JSON fields to match the CSV schema (e.g., opened_at -> timestamp).Insert into the same DB table used by the CSV importer.Phase 5: The Dashboard (Risk Grader)Instruction:Create route GET /dashboard.Status Gauge: Show latest Risk Score (Red/Green).Data Source Toggle: Add a label showing "Source: [CSV Audit | Live API]".Graph: Plot the cpu_load vs ticket_velocity data.6. Pre-Flight Checklist[ ] Google Cloud Key: Ensure key.json is linked in .env.[ ] BigQuery Dataset: Create aegisight_mvp.[ ] CSV Sample: Run your simulator script to generate a test_upload.csv file so you can test Option 1 immediately.